              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>EA has confirmed that <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/battlefield-6/" data-ref-id="5000-687940">Battlefield 6</a> will prioritize current-gen systems and PC, skipping out on PS4 and Xbox One.</p><p>In a press release following the game's multiplayer reveal, the publisher stated definitively that the next entry in its globe-spanning FPS will be arriving on October 10 exclusively on PS5, Xbox Series X|S, and PC. As for a possible Switch 2 appearance, a <a href="https://www.ea.com/games/battlefield/battlefield-6/faq" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">FAQ response</a> reads, "We currently do not have plans to release Battlefield 6 on Switch 2."</p>



    
