          <p><em>Now Playing:</em> Grounded 2 Early Access is GREAT... But Also More of the Same So Far</p>
      </div>
<p>To enjoy cross-play in Grounded 2, you'll need a <a href="https://signup.live.com/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Microsoft account</a>. After you've signed up and linked the accounts, you can check to play sure cross-play is enabled by heading to the Options menu. Scroll to the bottom and enable cross-play if needed, then you'll be all set and ready to jump in with your pals!</p><h2>Does Grounded 2 have cross-progression?</h2><p>There's more good news, too. <strong>Grounded 2 supports cross-progression as part of the Xbox Play Anywhere initiative as long as the game is purchased on the Microsoft Store or accessed via Game Pass</strong>. Those who purchase the game on Steam, for instance, won't be able to make use of cross-save functionality.</p><p>For those within Microsoft's ecosystem, however, Xbox Play Anywhere allows you to start the game on your Xbox, then pick up your save on PC--or vice versa. You can swap back and forth between the two at any time without worrying that your progress will be lost.</p><p>For more, check out our <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/grounded-2-guides-hub/1100-6533467/" data-ref-id="1100-6533467">Grounded 2 guides hub</a>.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
